---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Repl from '../../../../components/Repl';
---

<Layout title="Python in 5 Minutes" favicon="🔵">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to reading list</a>

    <h1>Python in 5 Minutes</h1>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">If you already know any programming language, you know most of Python.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Python vs Scheme side by side -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 80" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Python -->
        <text x="90" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="#34d399" font-size="10">Python</text>
        <text x="90" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="15"><tspan fill="#34d399">3</tspan> <tspan fill="#60a5fa">+</tspan> <tspan fill="#34d399">4</tspan></text>
        <text x="90" y="65" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.4">infix: operator between</text>
        <!-- Arrow -->
        <text x="180" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="14" fill-opacity="0.3">&#x2194;</text>
        <!-- Scheme -->
        <text x="270" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">Scheme</text>
        <text x="270" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="15">(<tspan fill="#60a5fa">+</tspan> <tspan fill="#34d399">3</tspan> <tspan fill="#34d399">4</tspan>)</text>
        <text x="270" y="65" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.4">prefix: operator first</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Variables and expressions -->
    <h3>Variables and expressions</h3>
    <p>No type declarations. No semicolons. Just assign and compute.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`x = 5
print(x + 3)
print(x * 2)
`} />

    <!-- 2. Functions -->
    <h3>Functions</h3>
    <p>Define with <code>def</code>. Indentation marks the body. <code>return</code> sends a value back.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`def square(x):
    return x * x

print(square(5))
print(square(12))
`} />

    <!-- 3. Lists -->
    <h3>Lists</h3>
    <p>Square brackets make a list. Index from zero. Slice with <code>start:end</code>. <code>len()</code> gives the length.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
print(nums[0])      # first element
print(nums[1:3])    # slice: elements 1 and 2
print(len(nums))    # length
`} />

    <!-- 4. Conditionals -->
    <h3>Conditionals</h3>
    <p><code>if</code>, <code>elif</code>, <code>else</code>. Indentation replaces braces.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`def classify(n):
    if n < 0:
        return "negative"
    elif n == 0:
        return "zero"
    else:
        return "positive"

print(classify(-1))
print(classify(0))
print(classify(7))
`} />

    <!-- 5. List comprehensions -->
    <h3>List comprehensions</h3>
    <p>Build a new list by transforming and filtering an existing one, all in one line.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`squares = [x*x for x in range(5)]
print(squares)

evens = [x for x in range(10) if x % 2 == 0]
print(evens)
`} />

    <!-- 6. Lambda -->
    <h3>Lambda</h3>
    <p><code>lambda</code> creates a small anonymous function. Combine with <code>map()</code> and <code>filter()</code> to transform sequences.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`square = lambda x: x * x
print(square(5))

print(list(map(lambda x: x * 2, [1, 2, 3])))
print(list(filter(lambda x: x > 2, [1, 2, 3, 4, 5])))
`} />

    <!-- 7. Dictionaries -->
    <h3>Dictionaries</h3>
    <p>Key-value pairs. Create with <code>dict()</code>, access by key, iterate over items.</p>

    <Repl client:visible initialCode={`ages = dict(alice=30, bob=25, carol=35)
print(ages["alice"])

for name, age in ages.items():
    print(name, "is", age)
`} />

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center text-sm text-gray-400 mt-10">
      That's enough to read every page on this site.
    </div>

  </main>
</Layout>
